<img border=0 src="/images/pr_head.gif" alt="Preparing for Competition">
<p>
<blockquote>

<!-- ****** insert content of page below ****** -->

Western Resources supports a transition to a competitive marketplace
that assures fairness to all and makes service reliability and safety
top priorities.
<p>
The transition to a competitive marketplace should:
<p>
<ul>
<li>Preserve existing standards of safety, reliability, and dependable electric service;
<p>
<li>Offer consumers the opportunity to shop for options that most closely meet their needs;
<p>
<li>Make affordable electricity available to everyone;
<p>
<li>Ensure that competition occurs on a 'fair and level' playing field;
<p>
<li>Provide open access for all retail wheeling competitors; and,
<p>
<li>Provide for a mechanism to fully recover 'stranded costs.'
<p>
</ul>
<p>
<b>Company Position</b><br>
John E. Hayes, Jr., Chairman of the Board and Chief Executive Officer,
Western Resources, Inc. <a href="../topics/wheel.stm">comments</a> before the Kansas Legislative Task Force
on Retail Wheeling July 10, 1997.

